title: Austin Armacost booted off Celebrity Big Brother by fellow housemates in cruel twist
text:
Austin Armacost booted off Celebrity Big Brother by fellow housemates in cruel twist Angie Best also lost her place on the show in Friday's live elimination Share Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now Austin Armacost booted off CBB by HOUSEMATES in cruel twist Share this video Get celebs updates directly to your inbox + Subscribe Could not subscribe, try again later Invalid Email 
Austin Armacost has become the second housemate to be eliminated from Celebrity Big Brother . 
The star was booted off the show by his fellow housemates in a cruel twist announced by Emma Willis this evening. 
During his exit interview, the US hunk admitted he was gutted to be out. 
He said: "There's a lot of massive over-analyisation amongst the all star housemates. For me, being runner up last time, the only place to go was up. And now I'm second out - it doesn't feel nice." 
Austin added: "It wasn't as fun this time round." Read More Chloe Ferry, Kim Woodburn and Jessica Cunningham join Celebrity Big Brother line-up as late arrivals 
At the start of tonight's episode, Emma explained that not one but two celebs would be leaving the house. 
Making matters worse for this year's line-up, it was up to the housemates to decide who would be losing their place in the competition second time round. Video Loading Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now Angie Best is eliminated from the Celebrity Big Brother House Share this video Watch Next The star was booted off the show by his fellow housemates in a cruel twist announced by Emma Willis (Photo: Channel 5) 
Emma explained: "The gates of hell are being swung open for our celebrities. No more Mr Nice Guy. 
"The housemates are expecting an eviction tonight but what they don’t know is there’s going to be a second shock eviction when the housemates will be forced to turn on each other and cull the dullest celebrity." 
Hesitantly, the remaining housemates decided that Austin should be boosted off the show. Austin didn't enjoy his CBB experience this time round (Photo: Channel 5) 
His departure came just minutes after Angie Best was eliminated by the public in the first eviction of the series. 
Calum Best's mum looked disappointed as Emma announced the results, confirming she was the first star of the series to get the boot. 
However, during her exit interview, she insisted she deserved to lose her place in the competition. Angie was also eliminated tonight (Photo: Channel 5) 
She said: "I thoroughly enjoyed Big Brother , but I couldn't help but think to myself, what am I doing here. I'm 64-years-old! 
"I've never done a reality show... Thank you Big Brother , it was an amazing experience but I am glad to be sat here." 
Angie added: "I went in there to spend time with my son [ Calum Best ]. But nine days in a bubble with all of those emotions and people - I've had enough now. Time for mum to go and let them get on with it." 
*Celebrity Big Brother returns to Channel 5 tomorrow at 9pm Like us on Facebook
